      "text": "XML “has been in a mainly stable relationship with the field of [[Technical Communication]] for over a decade”. In academia, scholars have praised XML as the foundation for information reuse, single sourcing, and, particularly, content management for more than a decade. Publications from the 2000s heralded that \"technical communicators will probably face a day when all organizational documents are saved in XML format\" and argued that \"technical communicators should be able to write, edit, and manage XML documentation, including XML tags, document type definitions (DTDs), XML schemas, and Darwin Information Typing Architecture ([[DITA]])\"."
