        "text": "Professional and technical communicators in the workplace probably have heard about the benefits of structured authoring for organizing content, collaborating across corporate silos, and future-proofing of information. In academia, faculty and students might have read about structured authoring as applied rhetoric to keep content consistent and tailored to the needs of specific audiences. In most cases, structured content implementations in the workplace and classroom depend on grammars of the Extensible Markup Language ([[XML]])."
